This paper discusses the limitations of wireless network densification in providing exponentially increasing data rates, which is a topic closely related to the fields of network information theory (cs.IT) and wireless networking (cs.NI). The paper also touches upon the potential impact on the technology landscape, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the need to prolong the limitations from occurring, which could involve security and cryptography (cs.CR) measures.
